Defendant Gregory C Maier in court with attorney Mark Emil Kershek.  Melissa J. Zilavy appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Defendant enters a guilty plea to Count 1.  Court finds defendant guilty.  The Defendant was sentenced to the following:

WITHHELD SENTENCE:

TERM OF PROBATION:  18 MONTHS

CONDITIONS OF PROBATION:  
*Maintain employment and/or combination of schooling 
*No contact with: victims or businesses listed in this case, 16CM82 or 16CF53
*DNA sample to be provided if not yet previously done.

RESTITUTION:  $4,412.81 to Ground Maintenance Services and $658.50 to Auto House (to be paid as a condition of probation - restitution to be paid before costs or fines);

FINE and COURT COSTS:  $1,548.00 (to be paid as a condition of probation);

DNA SURCHARGE:  $250.00 (to be paid as a condition of probation);

DRGOD:  $10.00 (to be paid as a condition of probation);

CONDITION TIME: 30 Days, STAYED; to be used at agent's discretion.  Agent to determine with or without non working hours.  

Felony warnings, voting rights and firearms warnings given.
